(April 2, 1953.)

(Republish.)

In the Matter of Joseph P. Ryan, Individually and as President of the International Longshoremen’s Association, as President of the Atlantic Coast District of the International Longshoremen’s Association, and as a Member of the Joseph P. Ryan Association, Appellant. Frank S. Hogan, as District Attorney of New York County, Respondent.

Order modified in accordance with the opinion herein and, as so modified, affirmed. Opinion Per Curiam. Present — Dore, J. P., Cohn, Callahan, Yan Yoorhis and Breitel, JJ.; Breitel, J., dissents and votes to dismiss the appeal in dissenting opinion. Settle order on notice. [See ante, p. 953.]
